<TR BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=3><TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="LEFT">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=9&show_all=1"><font size=2>&lt;&lt;&lt;&nbsp;DEC&nbsp;9</font></a></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="CENTER"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl"><font size=2>HOME</font></a></TD><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><a class="addthis_button" href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"><img src="http://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/v2/lg-share-en.gif" width="125" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"></script></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="RIGHT"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=11&show_all=1"><font size=2>DEC&nbsp;11&nbsp;&gt;&gt;&gt;</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR>
<TR HEIGHT=5><TD COLSPAN=3 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=5 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD>
<TD BACKGROUND="/black6.png">
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5><TR><TD>
	<TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=130 HEIGHT=130 SRC="chocs/choc_day_10.png" ALT="chocolate"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=190 SRC="globes/advent_globe_10.png" ALT="snowglobe"><table cellpadding=10 align="center" background="/black4.png" width=430><TR><TD><center><font size=6 color="#ffff00"><b><i>COMMANDO</i></b></font><br><font size=3 color="red"><b><i>15 days to Christmas</i></b></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><p>
I got my Spectrum+ in November 1985 - it was one of the infamous
Dixons Special Offer deal done with Sinclair Research to help tide over the
latter to 1986 - so, knowing little of the outside world when it
came to Speccy games, Christmas 1985 was unremarkable to anybody
outside my family beyond us exploring the machine's possibilities
whilst playing game after game after game of <i>Horace Goes Skiing</i>,
<i>Chequered Flag</i>, <i>Space Raiders</i>, and even <i>Castle Spellerous</i>. For some
reason each of us had full-length toweling dressing gowns, and for
some reason I remember my Saturdays would consist mainly of waiting
for my father to return from the weekly food shop before grabbing a
couple of fresh baps and making salami sandwiches for breakfast,
chomping on them whilst waiting for the games to load.
<TABLE ALIGN="center"><TR><TD VALIGN="top"><TABLE  WIDTH=200 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d10_1985_mag7.png" target="1985_mag7.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d10_1985_mag7_small.jpg" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=144></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>Your Sinclair's first MegaPreview. Umm. You'll need to tilt your head...</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE></TD><TD>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD><TD VALIGN="top"><TABLE  WIDTH=200 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d10_1985_rev3.png" target="1985_rev3.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d10_1985_rev3_small.jpg" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=148></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>Crash still has a rather basic page design at the end of 1985, even for the biggies.</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE>
